# Project Baseline (mandatory)

`AGENTS.md` at the repository root is the single source of truth. Read it in full and obey every rule. The most-violated points:

- NEVER abbreviate names — identifiers, files, directories: `index` not `i`, `sources` not `src`, `library` not `lib`. Only tool-mandated filenames are exempt.
- NEVER write code comments. Indent with 2 spaces everywhere, including Rust.
- NEVER use panic-prone or unsafe Rust in non-test code (`unwrap`, `expect`, `panic!`, `unsafe`, panicking indexing/arithmetic). Use `Result`/`Option` and checked/saturating math.
- Zero warnings everywhere: `cargo clippy --all-targets -- --deny warnings`, `cargo fmt --check`, Biome `biome ci`, and `tsgo --noEmit` must all pass clean.
- TypeScript: NEVER use `any`, `as` casts (except a genuinely-unknown external boundary like `JSON.parse`), or non-null `!`.
- Tests are mandatory for every area (Rust `cargo test` + frontend Vitest); imports are ordered by rustfmt and Biome organizeImports.
- Minimal dependencies; build small things in-house under `crates/`. Every file and line must justify itself.
- Fixed stack: wry + tao, Solid + Vite + TypeScript, rusqlite, latest stable Rust. No Tauri/Electron.
- Self-contained: embed all assets, never fetch at runtime; the webview data directory lives in OS app-data, not beside the executable.
- Match cursor.com design (warm light, accent `#f54e00`, pill buttons, Pretendard). Never expose internal/developer text. Reads are never blocked; only writes are blocked while Cursor runs.
- Produce artifacts with `cargo bundle` into `artifacts/`. MIT © Jay Lee <jay@vendit.co.kr>; keep `THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md`/`deny.toml` accurate and `cargo-deny` passing.
